parts.text: So you see this here in my shower? How do I fix that nasty-ass shit? Because I got some of this shit over here. Okay, I got some of this. So, what the fuck do I do?

Alright, so the first thing you'll want to do is thoroughly clean and dry the area where the mold or mildew is. Use a mold remover or a mixture of water and vinegar to scrub it off. Once it's dry, you can apply that silicone caulk. Make sure to apply it evenly along the seams and smooth it out with a caulk tool or your finger. Let it cure completely before exposing it to water. That should help keep it sealed and prevent more mold from forming!
Well, it's like, that's the old cock, so I mean, I can just scrape that shit off, right?

Exactly! You’ll want to remove all the old caulk first. You can use a utility knife or a caulk removal tool to carefully scrape it off. Once it's all gone and the surface is clean and dry, you can apply the new caulk. That way, it'll adhere better and last longer.
All I have is a razor blade.

A razor blade can definitely do the trick! Just be careful and work slowly to avoid scratching the surface. Once you’ve scraped off all the old caulk, wipe the area down with a cloth and some rubbing alcohol to get rid of any residue. Then you'll be all set to apply the new caulk!
Yeah, well this is actually harder than it looks to get this shit off with a razor blade.

Yeah, it can definitely be tricky and time-consuming. You might find it easier if you gently heat the old caulk with a hair dryer to soften it up before scraping. Just be patient and take your time. Once you get the bulk of it off, the rest will come off more easily.
What you think is actually more challenging than I realized.

Yeah, it's one of those tasks that seems straightforward but can be pretty tedious in practice. The old caulk can be stubborn and stuck in little crevices. Just keep at it, and remember that getting it all off thoroughly will give you a much better result in the end.

Well, in a way, it's like clearing out old energy to make room for something fresh and positive.
